summary: What is your most favorite (or Top 5 if you can't pick only one) Winteriron headcanons? What would you like to see more of,...
question: What is your most favorite (or Top 5 if you can't pick only one) Winteriron headcanons? What would you like to see more of, potentially? This can be fluff, angst, smut, ANYTHING GOES!
answer:
Honestly, I’m here for all WinterIron headcanons, BUT this is my list of favorites regarding our boys. As long as it has a happy ending then I will read/support it.

  • Tony noticing that Bucky likes to wear jackets and stay covered up so Tony goes out of his to buy him the softest blankets possible. Even going as far as getting custom footie pjs made of all of the Avengers costumes. Bucky likes wearing the Iron Man ones the most and Tony gets a Winter Soldier one so they wear them together during movie nights . That’s the fucking teeaaaaa.
  • Winter and Bucky are two separate personalities and Bucky doesn’t event realize that Winter is alive. Tony is the one who first finds out about Winter and the two end up clicking.
  • Bucky and Tony bonding over forced body modifications. Its depressing, but it brings them closer together.
  • Bucky being protective over Tony and standing up for him against the negative things the Avengers/reports say.
  • Bucky calling him “Darlin’” or “Sweetheart” and Tony fucking swooning.

Bonus

  • Tony getting drunk and confessing his feeling while Bucky just has a soft smile on his face. Like, those boys are soft and love each other.

description:
Ok, since people seemed to like my one-shot, I decided to go ahead and try my hand at a longer, chaptered fic. Again, please be patient, I’m still learning about the series as a whole, so there may be inaccuracies. But rest assured, I’m trying my best. XD I did say I would try and do more Hawkeye fics, so here we are~ Please feel free to let me know what you think!

Summary:  When Tony and Clint are sent on a simple scouting mission, the both of them expect a simple ‘get in, get out’ deal. Of course, things are never that easy, and it soon becomes clear they have more to worry about than the enemy on their trail.

Betas: @markofthemoros and @kagero-assassin

Words (so far): 3,343

Guess this means I need to make a Hawkeye picture now for my covers.

summary: if you want to go even further on the iron man lovefest, think about how in any other action-man movie, tony’s crawl to get the...
body:
if you want to go even further on the iron man lovefest, think about how in any other action-man movie, tony’s crawl to get the original arc reactor would have been a thing of power and strength and triumphant macho will against the odds, when our hero of the week roars with triumph as he staggers through his own strength to his goal. instead tony is weak and pitiable as he crawls across the floor - alone, we’re very much reminded that he’s going to die alone - and in the end he doesn’t even achieve his goal. he doesn’t reach the arc reactor; in the end it’s the dogged loyalty of dum-e that saves his life.

and yes, I realise that the mechanical arms are little more than machines, but the fact still remains that our hero here only wins because of the love he inspires in his pets robots

‘good boy’ absolutely slayed me too

title: The Second Soldier
body:
read it on the AO3 at http://bit.ly/2FU5pni

by FadedScream

The Winter Soldier and the five other Hydra agents that were given the Super Soldier Serum aren’t the only ones. During the war, HYDRA captured ten-year-old Katanya Sommer from her village and raised her to be a weapon as soon as it was safe to remove her memories.
Aside from the mental trauma, she was torn apart and put back together because of the engineer’s curiosity.
She spent seventy years as HYDRA’s doll, and as the Winter Soldier’s partner. Seventy years until she was found in a cryostasis chamber two months after the disaster at S.H.I.E.L.D.
And now she is caught up in the Avengers’ drama.
